video caption / description: I try to avoid the “this song means SO much to me” posts. When artists do that to me, it always feels like pressure. And truth be told, the ones that mean the most to me aren’t always the ones that resonate most with others. They’re not always the singles, or the even the best songs.  But every once in a while you get one and your gut tells you other people will feel it too. The words in your messages validated that. Thank you. It’s really beautiful to know you felt it too. You may have already seen this video, but I’ve chosen to share it again because I felt compelled to write about the unexpected reaction to it. Below is an excerpt but you can find the full piece on my Substack which is linked in my bio. —- “You can be a comedic actor trying to showcase your abilities in between auditions, or a 9-year-old who garners billions of views unboxing toys. You can film yourself doing your makeup, or read bite sized segments from your New York Times bestseller. By today’s definition, all of these people are the same — they are content creators.” —— I’ve been guilty of judgment and disdain for that term. I still don’t like it, but being suddenly lumped into that category of people has exposed me to an entirely new world of inspiring artists.  As I say in my piece, the music world has felt like “please look at me” whereas this new universe feels like “I made something for you.” All of this has left me grappling with decisions on new opportunities and my place in all of it, which I’m still questioning.  Lastly, I hope you don’t mind me having quoted you in the piece @blakeoftoday , but your wisdom was too brilliant not to pass on. As always, thank you for your words.

Day 16 of cassette covers. Song: Penny & the Quarters - “You and Me” My initial association with this tune was through the movie, Blue Valentine, but that eventually changed when my friends Mike & Jaclyn decided to get married. They had met as strangers at one of my shows many years prior, so leading up to the wedding, their friends reached out to me to see if I could play at the reception being as though I was a part of their story. Unfortunately, I couldn’t make it, but I sent a video of myself playing this song instead, which (initially unbeknownst to me) their friends played for them at their rehearsal dinner.  That’s now my association with this song. The story of the song and artist behind it is also incredible, so if you find a moment, that’s a great read. .  . . . . . . . . . . . @thenumerogroup #cover #coversong #1stvows #music #pennyandthequarters #numerogroup #fy #fyp #fypage

Old friends love you for YOU - not your accomplishments, your success, or anything external.❤️ After living in LA for a year, I returned home to visit Ohio. The unconditional love & acceptance I felt from my hometown friends really helped me see my own worth again, & helped me learn that anyone who treats me differently based on how well (or not well) I’m doing is NOT a real friend. It also helped me feel extra thankful for the people that have stood by me & loved me no matter what.🥰  #oldfriends #friends #song #friendship #queerartist #nonbinary

last year in late july/early august, we took a trip to Maine to decompress and meditate on things that were happening in our lives. we never planned to write any of these songs but as soon as we got there, they poured out. these are the most vulnerable songs we’ve written to date and we knew we wanted to wait until we were sure the right people would hear it before we released it. Our EP Maine is now yours forever, thanks for sticking with us and if you found us through Maine, we’re so glad you’re here. this song is called Piece of You. full performance is on our yt. #midwestemo #folk #emo
